oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Adron Hershell Massey
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Pvt. Adron Hershell Massey in uniform and wearing an overseaas cap. The image shows the subject from the waist up. There are no collar insignia nor shoulder patches on the tunic. Massey served in Co. E, 150th Inf. Regt., 38th Div. He was from Defeated, Smith County, Tenn. and was born in May, 1895. His unit never deployed overseas and he was discharged from service in June, 1919.
